  "doc_id": "31164",
  "text": "In the limit where sector 2 is R-symmetric, the contribution from sector 2 to SSM A-terms, B-terms, and gaugino masses is zero. Most relevant for our purposes, this implies that B µ and M 1 are nearly zero. The absence of a B µ term implies that the cancellation in Eq. (2.12) seen for G L cannot persist for the uneaten goldstino ζ. The absence of a M 1 term means that the LOSP decay to a γ/Z and ζ is highly suppressed. [CITATION_1] Both of these facts imply a large λ → h 0 + ζ branching fraction. Depending on the relative importance of the dimension 5 or dimension 6 operators, the mode λ → Z + ζ can be large as well.",
